---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About — AIdeaPulse" description="How AIdeaPulse finds and analyzes startup ideas for you every day.">
  <div class="space-y-8">
    <div>
      <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text-primary">About AIdeaPulse</h1>
      <p class="text-text-secondary mt-2 max-w-lg">
        We do the market research you don't have time for — every single morning.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-8 text-text-primary">
      <!-- What you get -->
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold mb-3">What you get</h2>
        <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Every morning, AIdeaPulse delivers AI-analyzed startup ideas to your feed.
          Each idea comes with a full brief — not just a title, but the data you need to decide whether to build it.
        </p>
        <ul class="text-text-secondary space-y-2">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-accent flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
            Market sizing (TAM/SAM/SOM) so you know the opportunity
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-accent flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
            Named competitors with landscape analysis
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-accent flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
            Build complexity rating and timeline estimate
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-accent flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
            Monetization angle with pricing suggestions
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-accent flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
            Confidence score (0-100) based on signal strength
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-accent flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
            Links back to the original discussions and sources
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- How it works -->
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold mb-3">How it works</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="flex gap-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-accent/10 flex items-center justify-center text-accent text-sm font-bold">1</div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold">We scan the internet every morning</h3>
              <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm mt-1">
                8 platforms — Reddit, Hacker News, Product Hunt, GitHub Trending, Dev.to, Lobste.rs, Google Trends, and NewsAPI. We pull the top trending discussions, product launches, and repos.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-accent/10 flex items-center justify-center text-accent text-sm font-bold">2</div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold">AI analyzes every signal</h3>
              <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm mt-1">
                A two-stage AI pipeline classifies each signal, then produces a full idea brief with market sizing, competitive landscape, build complexity, and a confidence score.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-4">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-accent/10 flex items-center justify-center text-accent text-sm font-bold">3</div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold">You get curated ideas in your feed</h3>
              <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm mt-1">
                Browse, filter, save, and rate ideas. Pro users also get a daily email digest with the top opportunities.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Why AIdeaPulse -->
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold mb-3">Why not just browse Reddit yourself?</h2>
        <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          You could — and many founders do. But you'd need to check 8 platforms daily, read hundreds of threads,
          and manually research each signal for market size, competitors, and feasibility. AIdeaPulse does all of
          that in an hour, every morning, while you sleep. By the time you check your feed, the analysis is done.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Founder note -->
      <div class="bg-surface border border-white/10 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold mb-2">Built by a builder</h2>
        <p class="text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          AIdeaPulse started as a personal tool — I wanted a better way to spot real demand signals
          without spending hours scrolling forums. The pipeline started as a script, then got AI analysis,
          then a feed, and now it's a product. If you're the kind of person who's always looking for the
          next thing to build, this is for you.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-text-secondary mt-3">— Kevin, founder</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="pt-4 border-t border-border">
      <a href="/" class="text-accent hover:underline text-sm">
        &larr; Browse ideas
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
